te data stores from production for safe migration testing",[219,256,257],{},"Accessible to the development team for pre-production verification",[207,259,261],{"id":260},"production","Production",[212,263,264],{},"Production is a full Kubernetes deployment managed through Helm charts:",[216,266,267,270,273,276],{},[219,268,269],{},"High-availability configuration with appropriate replica counts",[219,271,272],{},"Managed data persistence",[219,274,275],{},"TLS termination and ingress configuration",[219,277,278],{},"Monitoring and observability integration",{"title":280,"searchDepth":281,"depth":281,"links":282},"",2,[283,284,285],{"id":209,"depth":281,"text":210},{"id":242,"depth":281,"text":243},{"id":260,"depth":281,"text":261},"Development, staging, and production environment configuration.","md",null,{},{"icon":121},{"title":118,"description":286},"SJGZnRR58gN-s3ICMuJhNCDpDNOuSj7JJiGYvzvGPcQ",[294,296],{"title":113,"path":114,"stem":115,"description":295,"icon":116,"children":-1},"The Kinotic deployment pipeline from development to production.",{"title":123,"path":124,"stem":125,"description":297,"icon":126,"children":-1},"Command reference for the Kinotic CLI.",1775147362009]